The paper deals with algorithms for enumerating results on trees, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS). The use of automata and circuit-based algorithms suggests a connection to formal languages (cs.FL) and logic (cs.LO). The mention of tree balancing and updates to the underlying tree suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB). Finally, the focus on combined complexity and lower bounds suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC).
